Class Quantity<Q extends Quantity<Q>>

java.lang.Object
  org.ow2.chameleon.metric.Quantity<Q>
Type Parameters:
Q - the kind of quantity.
Direct Known Subclasses:
Acceleration, AmountOfSubstance, Angle, Area, Data, ElectricCapacitance, ElectricCharge, ElectricCurrent, ElectricPotential, ElectricResistance, Energy, Force, Frequency, Illuminance, Length, LuminousFlux, LuminousIntensity, Mass, MassicVolume, NoiseLevel, Power, Pressure, Temperature, Time, Velocity, Volume
public class Quantity<Q extends Quantity<Q>>
extends Object

This class defines what is a quantity. It offers methods to construct a quantity and methods to build make arithmetical operations on quantities.

Author:
Clement Escoffier, clement.escoffier@gamil.com

getKind

public String getKind()
Gets the quantity 's kind. The result depends on how the quantity is built:
  • if the `kind` parameter is set, returns the simple name of this class
  • if the `kind` parameter is not set, infer it by reflection
  • classes extending quantity mechanism that can't rely on the previous options must override this method.

Returns:
the quantity name, "unknown" if it can't be inferred.

add

public Quantity<Q> add(Quantity<Q> that)
Adds the current quantity with the given one. Before being added, the given quantity is converted to the current unit.

Parameters:
that - the quantity to add
Returns:
a new quantity adding the two quantities. The quantity's unit is the current unit.
